To write the formula =IF(E234="Lost",0,IF(E234="1 - Prospect",0.25,IF(E234="2 - Bidding",0.5,IF(E234="Awarded",1,FALSE)))) in Microsoft Lists, you can follow these steps:

1. Open the desired list in SharePoint.
2. Navigate to the column where you want to apply the formula.
3. Click on the column header and select "Column settings" from the dropdown menu.
4. Scroll down to the "Column Formatting" section and click on the "Format this column" link.
5. In the JSON formatting pane, you can write the formula.

Here's an example of how to write the formula in the JSON formatting pane:

```json
{
  "$schema": "https://developer.microsoft.com/json-schemas/sp/v2/column-formatting.schema.json",
  "elmType": "div",
  "txtContent": {
    "operator": "?",
    "operands": [
      {
        "operator": "==",
        "operands": [
          "@currentField",
          "Lost"
        ]
      },
      "0",
      {
        "operator": "?",
        "operands": [
          {
            "operator": "==",
            "operands": [
              "@currentField",
              "1 - Prospect"
            ]
          },
          "0.25",
          {
            "operator": "?",
            "operands": [
              {
                "operator": "==",
                "operands": [
                  "@currentField",
                  "2 - Bidding"
                ]
              },
              "0.5",
              {
                "operator": "?",
                "operands": [
                  {
                    "operator": "==",
                    "operands": [
                      "@currentField",
                      "Awarded"
                    ]
                  },
                  "1",
                  "false"
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
}
```

Make sure to replace "@currentField" with the appropriate column internal name or reference. Adjust the nesting and conditions based on your specific needs.

After writing the formula, save the changes. The column will display the corresponding values based on the conditions defined in the IF formula.
